<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I always treat my enchanter like royalty.  Even if we're hunting in the Dreadlands and multiple pulls can be easily avoided, I still give my chanter every HP and AC buff I've got (including symbol).  The way I look at it, if I spend a few pp on symbols for this enchanter and it happens to save his life once, it was worth it.<P>I always keep stun and root memmed, because that combo is a great way to get an angered mob off of an enchanter long enough for it to be easily mezzed.  I also make sure that my enchanter is always at no less than 80% health, and will not hesitate to heal him even if it will result in an over-heal.<P>I keep one eye on the group, and the other on the enchanter as a rule.  My first question whenever I join any group?  "Do I have an enchanter?"
</FONT>
