<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I also keep root up at all times.  I like working along side a chanter.  When I hear ADD, I move just as fast.  As the enchanter is mezzing a mob, I am rooting it.  That way, if they mez breaks, the enchanter can get back to it before the root is gone.  If the root breaks, it should still be mezzed, so I can refresh.  Also, while the tanks are busy with one mob, the chanter and I don't have to rely on the taunt.  If it comes on me, the enchanter is there mezzing it so I don't take much damage.  If the "add" moves to attack the enchanter, I'm there to root it, giving the enchanter space to step back and mez.  In a group, the "add" agro will always be on the casters, until the tanks can get around to the next mob.  So, let them whack away, while we do the "real" work.<P>Plus, it gives me something to do other than say "medding" and give Mana percentage reports.
</FONT>
