<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I want to thank Labirrynth, he's made me a better cleric.<P>Right now, if I'm grouped with a chanter he always gets my best buffs, and is the first one in the healing queue (right before the main tank). Clerics and chanters both generally realize that it will fall to them to keep the group alive in an overpull, so anytime I get attacked the chanter will mez a mob off me, and I'll root it off him.<P>Even if the main tank is under 20hp, and we still got 3 or more mobs on us, the chanter gets the first heal - that way he can mez all the mobs and give the group time to camp to clear agro.<P>Of course, if the chanter is an idiot and insists on trying to nuke the mob, ignoring the adds, he doesn't get a heal even if I'm FOM ("oops, I'm sorry, I was afk scratching my backside"), but that's a very rare case. 99% of chanters out there know what to do and do it well, it's the occasional ebayer who thinks that this game involves no skill that gets the shaft ;-)<P>Anyway, just wanted to agree with everyone here, keeping the chanter alive is paramount if you want to survive large fights.<P>Deian <The Chosen Few><BR>24 Cleric of Tunare<BR>Zeboxoruk
