<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
As a cleric I am very thankful that my RL wife play a druid.  So I will be responsible for healing eveyrone in the party except for myself and the enchanter, which she takes care of.  Being in the same room as we play makes it easier too, because if there is a reason that she isn’t going to be able to heal the enchanter....she can tell me instead of having to type a message.  Believe me, I know many of enchanters that be dead is she would have had to type that message to me as slow as she type hehehe.  But that usually works out nicely since enchanters get the tar beat out of the on a regular basis.  It is nice to know that my crack dealer/riot control has an angel watching over them....unless she goes on yet another coffee run LOL.<P>But I can’t remember the last time I have played without another healer in the group of some type and it is soooo much easier on the cleric if he has some help keeping the non tanks up.  I have yet to meet a tank that wasn’t a cleric mana sponge 8).<P>PS- No enchaters were harmed in the writing of this post.<P>--------------------<P>Craddix Mandrill<BR>Cleric of the 45th Season<BR>Prexus
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
